  "texts": [
    "For example, the presence of lymphocytes in tumor tissue is a useful prognostic biomarker that indicates the course of the disease in various types of cancer [3].",
    "Additionally, predictive biomarkers forecast response to specific treatments.",
    "One notable example is homologous repair deficiency (HRD), which can increase patients' susceptibility for treatment with Poly-ADP-Ribose-Polymerase (PARP) inhibitors [4][5][6].",
    "Usually, the routine acquisition of patientspecific features is typically limited to a select set of biomarkers, due to high costs, its time-consuming nature, and specialized equipment and expertise required for complex biological assays [7].",
    "Furthermore, many of these advancements remain accessible only to a limited number of cancer patients globally."
  ],
